Sure, here is an example of a single HTML page with an experimental navigation style for a restaurant website:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Experimental Restaurant Website</title>
<style>
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

.header {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 10px;
}

.navbar {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  background-color: #f8f9fa;
}

.nav-link {
  margin: 10px;
  padding: 5px 10px;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: #333;
}

.nav-link:hover {
  background-color: #e9ecef;
}

.hero {
  background-image: url('hero-image.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  height: 400px;
  text-align: center;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
  color: white;
}

.menu {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 20px;
}

.menu-item {
  margin: 10px;
  display: inline-block;
}

.footer {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 10px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="header">
<h1>Experimental Restaurant</h1>
</div>
<div class="navbar">
<a href="#" class="nav-link">Home</a>
<a href="#" class="nav-link">Menu</a>
<a href="#" class="nav-link">Reservations</a>
<a href="#" class="nav-link">Events</a>
</div>
<div class="hero">
<h2>Welcome to our Culinary Adventure</h2>
</div>
<div class="menu">
<h3>Our Menu</h3>
<div class="menu-item">
<img src="dish1.jpg" alt="Dish 1">
<p>Dish 1 Description</p>
</div>
<div class="menu-item">
<img src="dish2.jpg" alt="Dish 2">
<p>Dish 2 Description</p>
</div>
<div class="menu-item">
<img src="dish3.jpg" alt="Dish 3">
<p>Dish 3 Description</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="footer">
<p>&copy; 2021 Experimental Restaurant. All rights reserved.</p>
</div>
</body>
</html>
```

Please note that you will need to replace the placeholder images (`hero-image.jpg`, `dish1.jpg`, `dish2.jpg`, `dish3.jpg`) with actual images for this code to work properly. Additionally, you can further customize and enhance this code to fit your specific needs and design preferences.
